Title: The Elegant Universe: Superstrings, Hidden Dimensions, and the Quest for the Ultimate Theory
Author: Brian Greene
My Review: I enjoyed the backgrounds in quantum mechanics and relativity more than the primary topic of the book: string theory. String theory is certainly fascinating as a potential "theory of everything", but it's hard to assemble a primer on the subject for those of us that aren't theoretical physicists. It gets wild and abstract pretty quick.

Title: The Order of Time
Author: Carlo Rovelli
My Review: A succinct and powerful rumination on the nature of time, gravitation, and quantum theory. Because it's not overly technical, more philosophical, it was great in audio form.

Author: Joseph Campbell

Title: Cosmos
Author: Carl Sagan
My Review: An excellent popular science book. I would highly recommend to anyone as an introductory read on astronomy, physics, and the history of science. I'm amazed at how relevant even the advanced theoretical physics coverage is, for a book published nearly 40 years ago.
